Flux Data Summary

Trevor Williams

September 4, 2019

N2O Flux Data

This is a preliminary report on N2O Flux Data from the Willamette project. Many sources were referenced for the various tests employed including https://rcompanion.org/handbook/index.html.

This document will serve as a template for initial reporting of data from all fields and plots, including CO2 flux and water anlyses.

## data:  flux_data_n2o_cp$flux
## W = 0.34816, p-value < 2.2e-16

Null hypothesis for Shapiro-Wilk test, that data are from a normal distribution is rejected. First lets focus on the the Conventional VS Precicion Agriculture or Enhanced Efficiency Fertilizer

Conv. VS P.A.

First boxplot shows full range of data with outliers.

Second boxplot shows the central tendency of the data clearly, with 50% of the data indicated by the box, the median clearly visible as a line in the middle, and the IQ range +/- 1.5 indicated by the whiskers.

T-tests are for normally distrubted data around the mean.
